    "title": "Customizing time zone with TaskScheduler.getClock()",
    "body": "<p>From the documentation of <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/scheduling/support/CronTrigger.html#%3Cinit%3E(java.lang.String,java.time.ZoneId)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>CronTrigger(String expression, ZoneId zoneId)</code></a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note that such explicit time zone customization is usually not necessary, using <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/scheduling/TaskScheduler.html#getClock()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>TaskScheduler.getClock()</code></a> instead.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What is that supposed to mean? You can't set the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/time/ZoneId.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>ZoneId</code></a> of a <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/time/Clock.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Clock</code></a>.</p>\n"
